Key Match Events: Youssef Msakni scored a late 87th-minute penalty to give Tunisia a 1-0 victory over Malawi.
Post-Match Reflections: Tunisia coach Jalal Qaderi credited experience as a key factor in the win.
Malawi coach Patrick Mabedi was satisfied with his team's performance but acknowledged the need for improvement in attacking efficiency.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Lawrence Chaziya received a yellow card for fouling an attacker in the box, leading to the penalty.
Malawi will face Sao Tome and Principe on June 3, 2024, in their next qualifier match.
